{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The introduction of the Vision Transformer (ViT) [49] marked a pivotal shift by applying the transformer architecture-originally designed for natural language processing-directly to sequences of image patches.",
    "This approach fundamentally changed the paradigm of how models process visual information.",
    "Building on this, CLIP (Contrastive Language-Image Pre-training) [50] advanced the field by learning visual concepts through natural language supervision, enabling the model to adeptly handle various vision tasks with minimal task-specific training.",
    "Further extending these innovations, Stable Diffusion [51] ventured into generative art, providing tools to create intricate images from textual descriptions.",
    "The most recent breakthrough, Segment Anything [52], tackles image segmentation using deep learning to precisely identify and delineate multiple objects within images in ways that are contextually relevant."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The introduction of the Vision Transformer (ViT) [49] marked a pivotal shift by applying the transformer architecture-originally designed for natural language processing-directly to sequences of image patches.",
